No, it is not possible to enter a `try` bypassing the first block (broadly speaking). You can introduce a condition variable to work around this:
```cs
public void Example()
{
    bool flag = false;

    if (some_condition)
    {
        flag = true;
        goto TryStart;
    }

    ThrowMethod();
TryStart:
    try
    {
        if (flag)
        {
            goto Somewhere;
        }
        int j = 1;

    Somewhere:
        int k = 1;
        ThrowMethod();
    }
    catch
    {
        DoesNotThrow();
    }
}
```
Obviously, such a construct has suboptimal readability characteristics at best.

