In `Compiler::impImportBlockCode` method if opcode is `CEE_PREFIX1` firstly we change` codeAddr` and then calculate `opcodeOffs`:
```
case CEE_PREFIX1:
    opcode = (OPCODE)(getU1LittleEndian(codeAddr) + 256);
    codeAddr += sizeof(__int8);
    opcodeOffs = (IL_OFFSET)(codeAddr - info.compCode);
    goto DECODE_OPCODE;
```
The same situation for `PREFIX` label:
```
PREFIX:
    opcode = (OPCODE)getU1LittleEndian(codeAddr);
    codeAddr += sizeof(__int8);
    opcodeOffs = (IL_OFFSET)(codeAddr - info.compCode);
    goto DECODE_OPCODE;
```
In this case for following IL code:
```
constrained. var<u1>
callvirt instance int32 [System.Private.CoreLib]System.Object::GetHashCode()
```
`opcodeOffs` for `callvirt` points to the 2nd byte of the instruction, because after processing `constrained.` we goto `PREFIX` label.
I think we should firstly calculate offset and then change codeAddr (in this case offset points to the 1st byte of instruction as expected). Is it correct?

